[I] A pipeline data transfer meter

[T] pv (Pipe Viewer) is a terminal-based tool for monitoring the progress
[T] of data through a pipeline. It can be inserted into any normal pipeline
[T] between two processes to give a visual indication of how quickly data
[T] is passing through, how long it has taken, how near to completion it is,
[T] and an estimate of how long it will be until completion.

[U] https://www.ivarch.com/programs/pv.shtml

[A] Andrew Wood <andrew.wood@ivarch.com>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

